{"id":"worship","term":"Worship","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Homage rendered to God which it is sinful (idolatry) to render to any created being (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 34:14\">Ex. 34:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 2:8\">Isa. 2:8</a>). Such worship was refused by Peter (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 10:25\">Acts 10:25</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 10:26\">26</a>) and by an angel (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 22:8\">Rev. 22:8</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 22:9\">9</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 34:14","Isaiah 2:8","Acts 10:25","Acts 10:26","Revelation 22:8","Revelation 22:9"]}